Highly recommend this hidden south Asian gem in Bay Ridge. There wasn't enough time to take a picture of my food... we ate it too fast! I cannot wait to go back to try their tandoori, tikka, biryani and other tasty treats. We ordered take away and the employees were nice and helpful. We ordered the lamb vindaloo (extra spicy) and malai kofta with some naan and vegetable pakoras. The aroma filled the car as we raced home to have it for lunch. Our first bites we were so surprised... me with the spice of the curry, the flavor of the dish and quality of the meat of the lamb vindaloo and my partner with the fresh-made taste of the kofta balls and homestyle malai sauce. The naan reminded me of food I would get along Coney Island Ave or in Jackson Heights and the veggie pakoras were a huge and flavorful.

A true authentic Indian cuisine restaurant!  I rarely ever try Indian cuisine, but after this restaurant, I will DEFINITELY come back for more.  For one thing, the interior of this place is beautiful! It truly makes me feel as if I’m INSIDE the Taj Mahal. It adds onto the authentic vibe of the establishment.  This establishment gave free Papad (bread) and free dipping sauces on the side in the beginning, and free Firni (rice pudding) at the end. They were both absolutely delicious.  I ordered the Shahjahani Biryani and the Chicken Shree Mangal and they tasted really good. I really liked the Biryani and the curry chicken.  The bill was extremely affordable as well, taking into account the amazing interior, the freebies, and how well the staff treated us.  All in all, delicious food and great service

Great food and service... Been going  here for 8 yrs

A gem of a find in Bay Ridge. It's a nice space with wonderful attentive service. Loved how the table settings had the decorative sauces and sides presented in wonderful servicing dishes. The food is spot on and delicious. Authentic and flavorful. My go to items would be anything in the Tandor. The tandori chicken was tender with wonderful spices. The saag paneer (spinach and cheese) was spot on. You can tell the ingredients are fresh as the spinach pieces were still very noticeable and leafy. Great veggie dishes as well with the carrots and cauliflower dish with wonderful spices in the sauce. Plenty of complimentary side dishes provided with spicey pickles, cabbage, and a indian cracker. The naan bread was outstanding with a soft chewy interior and and nice exterior cooked up in the tandoor. It's a great place and very authentic. I'll definitely be back.
Went there once and can't wait to go back! Food is delicious! If you like Indian food this is only place to eat it!
Hands down my favorite Indian restaurant in all of NYC. You will find it hard to beat their food and price.
Very clean, food is very fresh and tasty, prices are very reasonable, service is really great, the atmosphere is very nice. Well deserved 5 stars

Intimate and cozy restaurant offering some delectable south east asian fare. They have a wide array of food to choose from, so fret not if your pescetarian, vegetarian or vegan. I have yet to try one dish from Taj Mahal that I did not enjoy. The food is flavorful and can be made as spicy as you'd like. I would recommend the biryani, tikka massala, and tandori dishes. For those nights you'd like to stay in, call 20 minutes ahead so you can drive by and pick up your order without the wait time. Note that they offer free valet service on busy nights, i.e. Friday and Saturday.
Food and service all the staff great
The best Indian restaurant I've ever seen in NY. Samosas, nan, curries......everything's so delicious.
Tried the Tikka Makhani - loved it.

Visiting with my son during the holidays, we took a chance on this restaurant. The place is beautifully decorated in a formal setting with white tablecloths, pink cloth napkins, romantic lighting. The menu prices were surprisingly  reasonable for what appeared to be an upscale restaurant. We tried the chicken tikka makhni and chicken tikka masala served with white rice and they were delicious! The nan bread tasted like it had just come out of the oven. But what impressed us the most was the service. Polite waiters in crisp white shirts and bow ties refilled our glasses continuously. When our waiter learned it was our first visit, he brought us appetizers and rice pudding dessert on the house. My son and I were very impressed with the food and service and would not hesitate to return.

I almost always order for delivery from this place rather than dining in, though I've been there in person a couple of times. The chicken biryani is fantastic and comes in such a large portion that I can get a couple more meals out of the leftovers. I also love their samosas and the vindaloo is pretty good too. Friendly service, nothing to complain about.
